(1) Pre-transfusion testing:
  • ABO/Rh typing (forward + reverse — confirm match);
  • Antibody screen (3-cell panel detects clinically significant alloantibodies);
  • Crossmatch (donor + recipient): immediate spin (ABO confirm), antiglobulin (full match if antibody+), electronic crossmatch (if validated);
  • Type & screen valid 72 hours post-transfusion/pregnancy (new antibodies);

(2) Component selection:
  • PRBC: ABO compatible (not necessarily identical for ABO if no whole blood); Rh-matched for Rh-neg recipients (especially women childbearing);
  • Platelets: ABO ideally matched (plasma in unit), Rh-matched for Rh-neg women childbearing (small RBC contamination → anti-D);
