Myelodysplastic Syndromes (MDS) — Classification + Management:

(1) WHO HAEM5 (2022) / ICC: classified by dysplasia lineage count, blast %, genetics, ring sideroblasts:
  • MDS with low blasts (< 5% BM, < 2% PB);
  • MDS with low blasts and SF3B1 mutation;
  • MDS with low blasts and isolated del(5q);
  • MDS with biallelic TP53 inactivation (poor);
  • MDS with increased blasts (MDS-IB1 5-9%, MDS-IB2 10-19%);
  • MDS, hypoplastic;
  • MDS, fibrotic;
  • MDS/MPN overlap; -

