Hypothyroidism: primary (TSH↑, T4↓) — Hashimoto most common. Central (low/inappropriate TSH). Sick euthyroid distinct. Biotin/macro-TSH/heterophile interfere. Levothyroxine 1.6 μg/kg empty stomach; recheck q6-8 wk; pregnancy ↑30%. Subclinical Tx criteria.

