(1) Palliative care definition (WHO): improves QoL of patients + families facing life-threatening illness through prevention + relief of suffering by early identification + assessment + treatment of pain + other physical/psychosocial/spiritual problems; NOT limited to end-of-life; integrated early improves outcomes (Temel JCO 2010 NEJM lung cancer);

